  "chunk_index": 35,
  "summary": "After a tense exchange with Xiyuan (Yuzu) regarding their relationship, Hagoromo (Kouzuki) agrees to meet her on the other side of the lake after sunset. While returning to his room, Hagoromo encounters MacArthur, who provocatively claims to be the best detective in Japan, surpassing Wakimura. MacArthur mentions he has spoken to Kanou regarding the disappearance of a client, though Hagoromo suspects Muto has simply abandoned the client to hide in the mountains. Before retreating to his room, MacArthur issues a cryptic warning to Hagoromo to pay attention to \"the twins.\"\n\nLater, around 4 pm, Jia arrives in a panic to report that Kaina and Wanli are missing. The household is thrown into chaos; Kaname attempts to maintain authority while Yashiro (Daya) is overcome with distress. MacArthur appears, having been eavesdropping, and claims to have an answer regarding the situation. He commands Shinobu and Shizuka to follow him, dismissively treating the emotional distress of the others, including Yasuko (Yuri) and Daya, with cold indifference.\n\nHagoromo and Kaname follow MacArthur through the courtyard and into the outer garden. They walk a significant distance toward a large, calm lake. MacArthur stops and points to the center of the lake, where a small white wooden boat with the number \"2\" written in blue on the bow is floating.",
